msg.msgText: A method call to set an object on a message failed because the input object type ({0}) is not supported. The object types that are supported are Boolean, Byte, byte[], Character, Double, Float, Integer, Long, Short, and String.

msgExplanation.p: The input object for calls to setObjectProperty(), writeObject(), or setObject() must be one of the following types: Boolean, Byte, byte[], Character, Double, Float, Integer, Long, Short, String.

msgUserResponse.p: When calling setObjectProperty() on Message objects, or when calling writeObject() in a BytesMessage or setObject() on a MapMessage, ensure that the object type is one of the following types: Boolean, Byte, byte[], Character, Double, Float, Integer, Long, Short, String
